X_i
E(X_i) = \mu
Var(X_i) = \sigma^2 > 0
E(\max X_i)
X_i
E(\max X_i)\geq \mu)
M_n=\max\limits_{1\leqslant i\leqslant n}X_i
\mathbb E(M_n)\geqslant\mu
\mathbb P(X_i=\mu+x)=\mathbb P(X_i=\mu-x)=a
\mathbb P(X_i=\mu)=1-2a
0\lt a\lt\frac12
x=\sigma/\sqrt{2a}
X_i
\sigma^2
M_n\in\{\mu-x,\mu,\mu+x\}
\mathbb P(M_n\ne \mu+x)=(1-a)^n
u_n(a)\to0
a\to0^+
 \mathbb E(M_n)\leqslant\mu+x\cdot (1-(1-a)^n)=\mu+\sigma\cdot u_n(a),\qquad u_n(a)=\frac{1-(1-a)^n}{\sqrt{2a}}. 
